SIMPLE: trochanter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trochanter
<hw>Tro*chan"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of two processes
near the head of the femur, the outer being called the <stype>great
trochanter</stype>, and the inner the <stype>small
trochanter</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The third joint of the leg of an
insect, or the second when the trochantine is united with the
coxa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trochanteric</ent>⟦br⟧
